Introduction

GOT the beat (Korean: 갓 더 비트; Japanese: ビートを得た) is a South Korean female supergroup formed by SM Entertainment. On December 27, 2021, SM Entertainment announced the group, featuring BoA, aespa's Winter and Karina, Red Velvet's Seulgi and Wendy, and Girls' Generation's Taeyeon and Hyoyeon.

GOT the beat revealed a special stage on January 1 2022 and debuted on January 3, 2022, with their first single "Step Back."

On January 16th, 2023, they made their comeback, with a new single called "Stamp On It."
